legacy.full_text: #SpringStories—Postal Delivery. China's postal industry development at a glance: steady expansion in terms of both business revenue and parcels handled in 2022 & the total revenue of China's postal industry expected to grow by 6 percent y-o-y in 2023. https://t.co/5OP6MiLj0R

#ChinaEconomy In 2022, China's outbound direct investment grew steadily despite external headwinds, rising by 5.2 % year on year to 985.37 billion yuan (146.5 billion dollars). Non-financial investment into countries along the B&R increased 3.3 % to 20.97 billion dollars. https://t.co/CKdHEnGJIC

#SpringStories—Sports. Let’s enjoy the winter sports boom ! A report on China's snow&ice tourism development predicts that the number of snow&ice leisure travelers in China is expected to exceed 300 mln in 2022-2023 and reaches 520 mln in three years. https://t.co/mzALN7CJLC

legacy.full_text:
#SpringStories—Sports. IOC's review at a glance: Beyond staging spectacular Games, Beijing 2022 was focused on delivering lasting social & economic benefits. @iocmedia
https://t.co/Q2knupK5XD

#SpringStories—Sports. Sincere thanks to IOC President Thomas Bach for hailing "impressive" legacy as Beijing 2022 marks one-year anniversary. @iocmedia https://t.co/KfGCLb9peO https://t.co/2WaB7FGF0V

#SpringStories—Sports. Fond memories last long. As a remarkable Olympic year went by, while recalling those exciting moments, I’m so glad to learn that Beijing and Hebei Province has jointly celebrated the 1st anniversary of Beijing 2022. Cheers✌ https://t.co/OkeoZLHq9S

#SpringStories—HEALTH. China stands ready to work with the international community to give full play to the unique advantages and role of traditional medicine including TCM to achieve Health For All. @WHO https://t.co/p6Us0nWAL1
#SpringStories—HEALTH. Since the outbreak of COVID-19, China has introduced TCM techniques to over 150 countries & regions, and provided ready-for-use TCM to those in need. https://t.co/RkNF4IP6xc

#SpringStories—HEALTH. Traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) is the most precious component of the Chinese civilization & a medical science developed in people’s daily life and during the fight against diseases over thousands of years. https://t.co/KWDXh874Km

#SpringStories—HEALTH. The decision to draft new global traditional medicine strategy 2025-2034 proposed by China & India has been adopted by the 152th @WHO EB Meeting, an accelerator for realizing health-related SDGs through application of traditional medicine. Congratulations ! https://t.co/I7P28Wah0v

#SpringStories－Meteorology. Today marks the 27th World Wetlands Day with the theme “Revive and Restore Degraded Wetlands”. We call for global consensus on prizing wetlands, respect for nature, and protecting the ecological security of wetlands. https://t.co/LYDg3Hh4es

#SpringStories－Meteorology. A Fuxing CR400BF-GZ train started its service at the highest latitude and in the coldest region in China, a technological breakthrough which makes transportation more smooth and convenient. https://t.co/WFdJRiIVJw

#SpringStories－Meteorology. From extreme floods to drought, from extreme heat to cold waves, weather and climate-related disasters affected millions and cost billions. Let’s work together to foster a community of life for man and nature.

#SpringStories－Meteorology. Beijing Climate Centre unveiled its selection of top 10 weather & climate events in 2022. According to WMO, such events are “tell-tale signs” and call for effective adapting actions to climate change. More at: https://t.co/lvLGftvxrF https://t.co/86UnwV1znJ
Today, I was delighted to attend Pakistan’s fourth #UPR, commended its human rights achievements, and extended my best wishes for its successful UPR cycle. https://t.co/mioDpqgwJi

#SPRINGSTORIES—China’s Economy. As China downgraded its management of COVID-19 and facilitated the smooth cross-border travel in early January, the outbound travel market, which had been almost dormant for the past 3 years, quickly recovered during the #SpringFestival. https://t.co/u29wR1EXq7

#SPRINGSTORIES—China’s Economy. Political, business leaders express optimism at Davos. IMF Deputy MD Gopinath hailed China's reopening as a positive sign to re-engage with the world, and an expected sharp recovery in economic growth from the 2nd quarter. https://t.co/d7uIq3cVBr

#SPRINGSTORIES —China’s Economy. Steady growth in 2022 despite epidemic resurgences&complicated external environment:
🟢3% YoY growth to a record high of ￥121.0207 tn(about $18 tn)
🟢industrial output increased 3.6% 
🟢fixed-asset investment rose 5.1%. https://t.co/8wE5XigMZu

#SPRING STORIES—China’s Economy. In the speech delivered at Davos, Chinese Vice Premier Liu He reaffirmed China's commitment to taking economic development as the primary & central task, and all-round opening-up, int'l cooperation with other countries.

#SpringStories—ICT. To accelerate the development of high-end, intelligent and green manufacturing, China will continue to take high-quality development as the primary task, focus on promoting structural adjustment, transformation and upgrading.
